  "texts": [
    "Many studies also calculated the dose from the original treatment plan.",
    "Approximately 1% of the dose was different, which is small compared to the uncertainty associated with the total dose over the entire treatment course (5%).",
    "In RT, DL-based methods generate relatively minor improvements in dosimetric accuracy compared to image accuracy and may not be clinically relevant.",
    "VMAT (Volumetric Modulated Arc Therapy) plans offer greater flexibility in dose calculations, particularly when dealing with image inaccuracies, especially in uniform areas like the brain.",
    "In VMAT, random image inaccuracies tend to balance out within an arc, but it's worth noting that there's a non-linear relationship between random image inaccuracies and dosimetric errors."
